  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bangladesh: Combating Trafficking and Exploitation of Vulnerable Workers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center combats human trafficking in Bangladesh, including forced labor, debt bondage and bonded labor, particularly among garment workers. The Solidarity Center has been engaged with more than 180,000 garment workers around the world over the last five years, supporting their efforts to exercise their rights and gain dignity at work.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Working with civil society organizations, the Solidarity Center advocates for the implementation of legislation to protect the rights of migrant workers, to strengthen measures against fraudulent labor recruiters and to establish an information center where prospective migrant workers can receive information on safe migration as well as services available in destination countries.</narrative>
  </description>
